WEBVTT

00:07.808 --> 00:09.510
(SIGHS)

00:16.016 --> 00:18.486
This is
Andrews' fault.

00:18.519 --> 00:20.354
Agreed.

00:20.388 --> 00:23.057
The bourbon may also bear
some responsibility.

00:23.091 --> 00:24.358
Agreed.

00:25.959 --> 00:27.361
You said "fault."

00:28.896 --> 00:31.799
You don't regret
that we...
No, not at all.

00:31.832 --> 00:34.001
(CHUCKLES)
(CHUCKLES) Seriously.

00:34.702 --> 00:36.604
It was...

00:36.637 --> 00:37.805
Pretty great.

00:38.272 --> 00:40.074
Yeah.

00:40.108 --> 00:42.410
And definitely shouldn't
happen again.

00:43.344 --> 00:45.813
No, it shouldn't.

00:45.846 --> 00:47.715
It'd make things
too complicated at work.

00:49.750 --> 00:51.519
Let's chalk it up
to, uh,

00:51.552 --> 00:54.522
"Andrews screwed us, so we
screwed each other" impulse.

00:54.555 --> 00:56.957
(CHUCKLES)

00:56.990 --> 00:59.727
I gotta get going.

00:59.760 --> 01:01.195
I'm covering
the E.R. today.

01:01.229 --> 01:04.365
Ooh, right before
Christmas?

01:04.398 --> 01:06.500
Gonna be a madhouse.

01:06.534 --> 01:08.702
Yeah.

01:08.736 --> 01:13.574
(OVER SPEAKERS)
* I love those
J-I-N-G-L-E bells

01:13.607 --> 01:19.447
* Oh, those holiday
J-I-N-G-L-E bells

01:19.480 --> 01:21.081
* Those happy

01:21.115 --> 01:25.619
* J-I-N-G-L-E
B-E- double L-S

01:25.653 --> 01:30.224
* I love those
J-I-N-G-L-E bells

01:30.258 --> 01:32.025
* Oh

01:32.059 --> 01:35.028
* Jingle bells, jingle bells

01:35.062 --> 01:37.765
* Jingle all the way

01:37.798 --> 01:40.201
* Oh, what fun
it is to ride... *

01:40.234 --> 01:43.937
(ELECTRIC BUZZING)

01:45.038 --> 01:46.640
What is that noise?

01:48.108 --> 01:49.543
"Jingle Bells"?

01:49.577 --> 01:51.245
Two ambulances coming in,
back-to-back.

01:53.447 --> 01:55.416
Hey. I need you on
your game today, Murphy.

01:55.449 --> 01:56.484
Okay.

01:58.152 --> 01:59.720
(SIREN WAILING)

01:59.753 --> 02:01.589
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYS)

02:01.622 --> 02:05.326
**

02:05.359 --> 02:07.295
Uh, male,
mid-30s,

02:07.328 --> 02:08.562
found unresponsive
in Arrivals.

02:08.596 --> 02:10.498
Restarted his heart
on site. Low O2,

02:10.531 --> 02:12.633
wheezing, significant airway
resistance to the bag mask...

02:12.666 --> 02:14.768
We need more hands
on deck. STAT.
I've been calling,

02:14.802 --> 02:16.103
everyone's left town
for the holidays.

02:16.136 --> 02:17.338
Reznick's around.

02:17.371 --> 02:18.606
Weird you know that,
but glad you do.

02:18.639 --> 02:19.807
Get Reznick in here.
On it.

02:19.840 --> 02:21.942
Take him to Bay 4.
Murphy, I need you with me.

02:23.244 --> 02:24.478
What do we got?

02:24.512 --> 02:26.747
This is Marianne Southam,
she collapsed
in Baggage Claim.

02:26.780 --> 02:28.148
Both patients came
from the airport?

02:28.182 --> 02:29.650
It's that time of year.
Everyone's traveling.

02:29.683 --> 02:31.485
Right leg
is red and swollen.

02:31.519 --> 02:33.153
She's complaining of chest
pains, shortness of breath,

02:33.187 --> 02:34.488
and she has
a low-grade fever.

02:34.522 --> 02:36.424
Did you just get
off a long flight?

02:36.457 --> 02:38.359
(OUT OF BREATH)
20 hours, from Malaysia.

02:38.392 --> 02:41.329
Deep vein thrombosis formed
while she was seated,

02:41.362 --> 02:43.130
that explains the red leg
and the fever.

02:43.163 --> 02:45.065
Part of the clot broke off,
traveled to her lung,

02:45.098 --> 02:47.935
that explains the chest pain.
Pulmonary embolism.

02:47.968 --> 02:49.203
(FLATLINE)
We lost
his pulse again!

02:50.338 --> 02:52.139
Take Marianne to Bay 5.

02:52.172 --> 02:54.242
I'll talk you through managing
a pulmonary embolism.

02:54.275 --> 02:56.377
(FLATLINE CONTINUES)
I'm gonna light him up.

02:56.410 --> 02:57.678
(PADDLES WHINE)
Clear.

02:57.711 --> 02:58.879
(THUMP)

03:00.514 --> 03:02.082
(HEARTBEAT BEEPING STEADILY)

03:02.115 --> 03:03.351
Got a rhythm.
Barely.

03:03.384 --> 03:04.652
He can't live
on 30 beats a minute.

03:04.685 --> 03:06.620
His lungs are too stiff
to pre-oxygenate.

03:06.654 --> 03:08.756
Fiberoptic blade
and a 7.5 ET tube.

03:10.558 --> 03:14.328
Murphy, anti-coagulate her
with a 5,000-unit
heparin bolus.

03:14.728 --> 03:20.801
**

03:20.834 --> 03:22.970
Set the ventilator
to assist control.

03:26.039 --> 03:29.343
Heparin bolus infused.
Fever's spiking
at 103.5.

03:29.377 --> 03:31.345
Could be ARDS
from a viral pneumonia.

03:31.379 --> 03:33.013
Get a chest X-ray.
(MONITOR BEEPS RAPIDLY)

03:33.046 --> 03:35.148
(FLATLINE)
Lost him again.

03:36.183 --> 03:39.353
O2 SAT is 92.

03:39.387 --> 03:41.021
Your chest pain
should be getting better.

03:41.054 --> 03:42.690
It is.
Thank you.

03:42.723 --> 03:44.124
Peak airway pressure's 50.

03:44.157 --> 03:46.694
Switch the ventilator
to PRVC.

03:46.727 --> 03:48.128
Pushing I.V. epinephrine.

03:48.161 --> 03:51.565
Now you need to insert
a central line in case
we go to thrombolysis.

03:51.599 --> 03:57.371
**

03:57.405 --> 04:03.076
**

04:03.110 --> 04:04.244
I need you, Murphy.

04:07.114 --> 04:08.516
Still V. Fib.

04:08.549 --> 04:09.917
Push 300 of amiodarone.

04:10.250 --> 04:16.857
**

04:16.890 --> 04:18.526
Asystole.
He's still not responding.

04:18.559 --> 04:21.762
That's over 30 minutes
of brain and cardiac hypoxia.

04:21.795 --> 04:23.731
(FLATLINE CONTINUES)

04:26.199 --> 04:27.267
Stop compressions.

04:28.936 --> 04:30.338
(SIGHS DEEPLY)

04:30.371 --> 04:32.139
Time of death, 10:07.

04:33.006 --> 04:34.408
(BEEPING STOPS)

04:38.579 --> 04:40.814
Have you had contact
with this man?

04:42.950 --> 04:44.652
He was on my flight
from Malaysia.

04:44.685 --> 04:48.989
They both have
vesicular rashes
on their necks.

04:50.090 --> 04:52.560
Whatever infection killed him,
she may have it, too.

04:53.126 --> 04:59.967
**

05:00.000 --> 05:02.102
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

05:02.135 --> 05:07.408
**

05:12.012 --> 05:13.381
DR. LIM: This is a negative
pressure room,

05:13.414 --> 05:14.982
designed so no air
flows out.

05:15.015 --> 05:16.917
Keeps germs
from spreading.

05:16.950 --> 05:18.552
Because whatever I have
is gonna kill me,

05:18.586 --> 05:19.853
just like the man
from the plane?

05:19.887 --> 05:22.122
Your symptoms are not
as severe as his.

05:23.524 --> 05:25.292
Although, yours
will probably get worse

05:25.325 --> 05:27.695
as the virus progresses.

05:27.728 --> 05:30.330
We don't know for sure
whether you have
the same thing.

05:30.364 --> 05:33.934
We know nothing about him,
his condition, or his history.

05:33.967 --> 05:35.436
When did you start
feeling sick?

05:35.836 --> 05:36.870
On the plane.

05:36.904 --> 05:38.472
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

05:38.506 --> 05:40.941
I've never even been
outside the U.S. before.

05:40.974 --> 05:43.477
My ex-husband hated
to travel and...

05:43.511 --> 05:44.612
(COUGHING)

05:47.681 --> 05:50.217
Was the man who died
sitting near you?

05:51.284 --> 05:54.154
No, he was six or seven rows
in front of me.

05:56.457 --> 05:58.426
Were you ever physically
close to him?

05:58.459 --> 06:01.429
Say, waiting for the restroom
or in line to board?

06:01.462 --> 06:04.031
No, I think he slept
almost the entire flight.

06:04.064 --> 06:08.101
That suggests the virus can
be transmitted in the air.

06:09.403 --> 06:10.971
Which means everyone
in the plane

06:11.004 --> 06:13.441
and this emergency room
has been exposed.

06:13.474 --> 06:18.345
**

06:18.378 --> 06:19.713
We'll start conditioning
tomorrow,

06:19.747 --> 06:21.314
so we use chemo and
total body irradiation to...

06:21.348 --> 06:24.084
To wipe out my crappy
leukemia-producing bone marrow

06:24.117 --> 06:26.854
so you can replace it
with some good stuff.
Well said.

06:26.887 --> 06:29.690
Looks like your dad's good
to go on his marrow donation.

06:29.723 --> 06:30.724
Please don't
call him that.

06:32.493 --> 06:35.463
Bob Cravens walked out on me
and my mom when I was four.

06:35.496 --> 06:37.998
His biological material
gave me life,

06:38.031 --> 06:39.332
and apparently
he's gonna save me,

06:39.366 --> 06:40.400
but he's not my dad.

06:41.569 --> 06:44.438
Any unusual complaints or pain
we should know about?

06:45.606 --> 06:46.940
I've been tired.

06:46.974 --> 06:48.676
And the last day, achy,

06:48.709 --> 06:51.411
kind of stiff...
Standard leukemia woes.

06:52.980 --> 06:54.114
Anywhere
in particular?

06:55.048 --> 06:57.585
My neck, left arm.

06:57.618 --> 06:59.787
Right, Chris, you're
having a heart attack.

07:00.754 --> 07:02.923
N-No.
My chest feels fine.

07:02.956 --> 07:04.424
We need to get you up
to radiation right away.

07:04.458 --> 07:06.093
Call and let them know
we're coming.

07:06.126 --> 07:07.861
Get his donor in here.

07:07.895 --> 07:09.597
How is radiation gonna help
a heart attack?

07:09.630 --> 07:12.666
Your blockage is most likely
excess blast white cells.

07:12.700 --> 07:14.101
The best way
to clear out your heart

07:14.134 --> 07:15.135
is to treat your leukemia.

07:16.904 --> 07:18.939
It's what we planned.
Just a day early.

07:18.972 --> 07:21.942
**

07:22.810 --> 07:24.612
It might not be airborne.

07:24.645 --> 07:26.313
Maybe both passengers
were already infected

07:26.346 --> 07:27.748
when they got on the plane.

07:27.781 --> 07:29.883
Marianne said she felt fine
before the flight.

07:29.917 --> 07:31.919
But even if she did
contract it on the plane,

07:31.952 --> 07:33.453
it could've been
through a shared water cup

07:33.487 --> 07:34.555
or napkin...

07:34.588 --> 07:36.456
Which would make
a quarantine unnecessary.

07:39.292 --> 07:41.428
I'll call the Public
Health Department, the CDC,

07:41.461 --> 07:42.863
they may want
to track the passengers

07:42.896 --> 07:44.431
and anyone they
came into contact with.

07:45.833 --> 07:47.167
Keep me up to date.
Okay.

07:49.269 --> 07:50.771
Hey. I'm done.

07:51.338 --> 07:53.073
Jill, are you still on?

07:53.106 --> 07:55.609
Get me the CDC
and a change of clothes.

07:55.643 --> 07:57.545
I'm coming in.

07:57.578 --> 07:59.279
DR. REZNICK:
Thanks for getting me
called in, Tyler.

07:59.312 --> 08:01.348
You're welcome.
That was sarcasm.

08:01.381 --> 08:03.316
Oh, was it?
If this turns into a crisis,

08:03.350 --> 08:04.752
where else
would you want to be?

08:06.119 --> 08:07.821
I hear you're having
some stomach pain?

08:07.855 --> 08:09.122
It hurts a lot.

08:09.156 --> 08:11.925
I figured it was probably
the candy canes,
but I took some Pepto.

08:11.959 --> 08:13.026
Didn't help at all.

08:13.060 --> 08:14.562
How many candy canes
we talking?

08:14.595 --> 08:16.196
Three or four... Dozen.

08:16.930 --> 08:17.965
Of the little ones.

08:17.998 --> 08:19.432
They pass them out
at the mall where I work.

08:19.466 --> 08:21.368
I like to munch on them.
Keeps me in character.

08:21.401 --> 08:23.170
Sounds like you might
be overdoing it.

08:23.203 --> 08:24.638
Take off your shirt.

08:25.839 --> 08:27.775
How did you know I was
still in town?

08:30.043 --> 08:33.146
Because the holidays are
"an obligatory performance

08:33.180 --> 08:34.615
"where families buy
each other gifts

08:34.648 --> 08:35.949
and pretend everything
is perfect."

08:35.983 --> 08:37.918
Which is why you tell yours
you have to work every year

08:37.951 --> 08:39.620
even when you don't.

08:41.689 --> 08:43.156
He's a good listener.

08:44.892 --> 08:46.326
What's that scar from?

08:47.094 --> 08:48.829
Rudolph is an ass.

08:49.730 --> 08:51.632
(CHUCKLES)
It's a minor bowel resection

08:51.665 --> 08:53.867
for diverticulitis
eight months ago.

08:53.901 --> 08:55.803
Oh, we need to do
a contrast CT.

08:57.805 --> 08:59.006
You need
to come with me.

08:59.973 --> 09:02.676
Dr. Lim,
he has it, too.

09:02.710 --> 09:04.077
There, on his neck.
A rash.

09:04.111 --> 09:05.178
It wasn't there
earlier.

09:08.181 --> 09:10.784
It hasn't fully developed,
but it could be
the same thing.

09:10.818 --> 09:12.485
It can't be.
I had on a mask, gloves...

09:12.519 --> 09:15.022
Did you keep on the mask
the whole time?

09:15.055 --> 09:17.324
Not...
With airborne diseases,
that's important...

09:17.357 --> 09:18.726
(ALARM BEEPS LOUDLY)

09:18.759 --> 09:20.227
It's Marianne.
Her O2 SATs are crashing.

09:20.260 --> 09:21.929
Get another dose of
I.V. methylprednisolone.

09:22.863 --> 09:24.732
(MACHINE BEEPING)

09:24.765 --> 09:26.499
We need to move up
the transplant.

09:26.533 --> 09:28.068
No, it doesn't
change anything.

09:29.136 --> 09:31.739
You'll be anesthetized,
you won't feel a thing

09:31.772 --> 09:33.406
and when you wake up,

09:33.440 --> 09:35.943
your son
will be on his way
to being healthy.

09:36.376 --> 09:38.045
(BRAKES SQUEAL)

09:41.548 --> 09:43.216
We'll see you soon.

09:43.250 --> 09:45.018
(CAR DOOR CLOSES)
(LAUGHS)

09:46.053 --> 09:48.055
Sorry I couldn't meet you
at the airport.

09:48.722 --> 09:50.457
That's
a cool t-shirt.

09:50.490 --> 09:52.525
It probably freaks
you out, right?

09:52.559 --> 09:56.063
Like, "is he gonna
gender-transition
or something?"

09:56.096 --> 09:58.065
No, if that's your thing,
I'm cool.

09:59.900 --> 10:01.168
(INHALES DEEPLY)

10:01.201 --> 10:02.235
How long am I stuck here?

10:02.269 --> 10:03.603
Just for the rest
of this shift.

10:03.637 --> 10:05.272
And then I'm out of here
for three days.

10:05.305 --> 10:07.240
There's a new
rock-climbing gym
we can check out,

10:07.274 --> 10:08.608
and the batting cages.

10:09.743 --> 10:11.011
I'm good.

10:11.044 --> 10:13.113
I got a season of
"Rick and Morty" on my phone.

10:16.984 --> 10:18.551
(SIGHS)

10:18.585 --> 10:20.020
DR. LIM: Clear.
(PADDLES WHINE)

10:20.053 --> 10:21.221
(THUD)

10:21.254 --> 10:22.389
(FLATLINE)

10:22.422 --> 10:23.791
**

10:27.060 --> 10:28.128
(SIGHS)

10:28.161 --> 10:30.530
That's six rounds of defib.
And 30 minutes of CPR.

10:32.132 --> 10:34.434
Okay, Dr. Murphy,
you can stop.

10:36.336 --> 10:37.671
(FLATLINE STOPS)

10:38.839 --> 10:40.808
(MELANCHOLY MUSIC PLAYS)

10:40.841 --> 10:43.677
**

10:48.982 --> 10:50.751
DR. LIM: I just spoke
with Dr. Andrews.

10:50.784 --> 10:53.286
We're on soft quarantine
while he consults the Board.

10:53.320 --> 10:56.289
Call dispatch, put all
ambulances on diversion.

10:56.323 --> 10:57.991
Do your best to stop
all walk-ins.

10:58.025 --> 11:00.928
Say we're at capacity
and send them to County.

11:00.961 --> 11:02.129
Stall all discharges.

11:02.162 --> 11:04.798
Tyler stays in isolation
and on antivirals.

11:04.832 --> 11:07.367
Fever is likely
the next stage,
so keep a close eye.

11:07.400 --> 11:08.668
What else
are we dealing with?

11:08.702 --> 11:11.071
I always have lunch
by 2:00.

11:11.104 --> 11:13.807
It's 2:15.
I need to eat.

11:13.841 --> 11:15.709
I've got a banana in my bag
if you want it.

11:15.743 --> 11:16.944
A banana isn't lunch.

11:16.977 --> 11:18.712
A turkey sandwich and milk
is lunch.

11:18.746 --> 11:20.513
Dr. Murphy,
patients first,

11:20.547 --> 11:22.149
then we'll work
on that sandwich.

11:22.182 --> 11:24.184
What else?
60-year-old woman
with angina,

11:24.217 --> 11:25.518
visiting her family
for the holidays.

11:25.552 --> 11:27.620
Forgot her
blood pressure meds.
Came in for a prescription.

11:27.654 --> 11:30.557
Her refill
just got delayed.
What else?

11:30.590 --> 11:32.826
The crib was almost finished
when the screwdriver slipped.

11:32.860 --> 11:34.995
My family doctor's closed
for the holidays.

11:35.028 --> 11:36.830
They would've sent you
here anyway.

11:36.864 --> 11:39.299
This type of injury can
cause permanent damage.

11:39.332 --> 11:42.535
Makes me feel less guilty
for bringing my baby
into a germ pit.

11:44.537 --> 11:45.538
No offense.

11:47.174 --> 11:48.608
Guessing this is
your first?

11:49.676 --> 11:52.112
My husband and I
waited a long time.

11:52.145 --> 11:54.114
I want everything
to be perfect.

11:54.147 --> 11:57.150
Which, as my husband
reminds me,
is impossible.

11:57.184 --> 12:00.420
Yet, my birth plan
is five pages long.
(CHUCKLES)

12:01.688 --> 12:03.556
All closed up.
(SIGHS)

12:03.590 --> 12:04.925
So I can go home?

12:06.026 --> 12:08.161
Not before
we do a nerve study.

12:08.195 --> 12:10.063
I would hate for you to lose
feeling in your fingers.

12:11.231 --> 12:13.500
SECURITY GUARD 1:
You can't leave.

12:13.533 --> 12:15.535
KELLAN: (SCOFFS) I'm sorry.
What?
Hospital policy.

12:15.568 --> 12:17.370
Look, I'm...
I'm not a patient.

12:17.404 --> 12:19.606
All right, I just came
down here to get some chips.
My dad's a doctor.

12:19.639 --> 12:21.341
Who's your dad?
Dr. Alex Park.

12:22.109 --> 12:23.343
Can you call him?

12:23.376 --> 12:25.578
My phone's
charging upstairs.

12:25.612 --> 12:27.781
I'll call him, so he knows
where to come find you
when he's free.

12:27.815 --> 12:29.216
But for now,
you've got to stay put.

12:30.784 --> 12:33.186
Why?
Because I'm older
than you.

12:35.923 --> 12:36.957
(SCOFFS)

12:41.261 --> 12:43.596
Find the employee
contact list,
call Park.

12:43.630 --> 12:45.899
He should know
where his son is.
Sure.

12:45.933 --> 12:48.969
**

12:49.002 --> 12:51.371
(MACHINE WHIRRING)

12:51.404 --> 12:54.774
CHRIS:
I feel so much worse than when
I was having a heart attack.

12:54.808 --> 12:55.943
DR. MELENDEZ:
I don't doubt it.

12:55.976 --> 12:57.878
Because of the urgency
of your situation,

12:57.911 --> 13:01.581
we used combined
leukapheresis,
chemo, and radiation.

13:01.614 --> 13:03.450
You're no longer at risk
for another heart attack
or stroke.

13:03.483 --> 13:06.119
And I also no longer
have an immune system.

13:08.688 --> 13:10.757
(SIGHS) My donor's
on his way, right?

13:10.790 --> 13:12.392
I spoke with him.
He said he was
getting in his car.

13:13.293 --> 13:14.627
When was that?

13:15.829 --> 13:17.030
I'll follow up.

13:18.165 --> 13:19.766
**

13:19.799 --> 13:21.668
(DOOR OPENS, CLOSES)

13:22.870 --> 13:23.971
(SIGHS)

13:24.004 --> 13:26.940
(SOFTLY) He's still finding
new ways to let me down.

13:26.974 --> 13:27.975
(SIGHS)

13:28.408 --> 13:29.877
**

13:31.011 --> 13:33.380
I thought you guys
were gonna do a C.T.

13:33.413 --> 13:35.983
We're doing
a KUB X-ray instead.

13:36.016 --> 13:37.250
It's almost as good.

13:38.118 --> 13:39.853
Why would you
go with "almost"?

13:46.193 --> 13:47.527
(ELECTRIC BUZZING)

13:57.204 --> 13:58.471
Can you hear that?

14:01.308 --> 14:03.843
Hear what?
Excuse me.

14:03.877 --> 14:05.178
I'm looking
for a patient.

14:05.212 --> 14:06.313
You'll need to speak
with a nurse.

14:06.346 --> 14:07.981
I've been waiting
to speak to a nurse.

14:08.015 --> 14:10.450
You must hear that.
The light is buzzing.

14:10.483 --> 14:11.851
I don't hear anything.
It's loud

14:11.885 --> 14:13.286
and very distracting.

14:13.320 --> 14:15.488
It needs to be fixed.

14:26.033 --> 14:27.300
You like Italian?

14:28.468 --> 14:29.569
La Nostra?

14:30.070 --> 14:31.638
It's great.

14:32.372 --> 14:34.341
Barbecue? Ethiopian?

14:34.374 --> 14:35.742
DR. REZNICK: What are you
talking about?

14:36.176 --> 14:37.510
(CHUCKLES)

14:37.544 --> 14:40.180
Where we're
going on our date.

14:40.213 --> 14:43.216
You haven't asked me on one,
and I haven't said yes.

14:43.250 --> 14:44.417
(CHUCKLES)

14:44.451 --> 14:47.487
Who turns down the request
of a man trapped in isolation?

14:50.790 --> 14:52.692
What about sushi?
Everybody likes it.

14:53.726 --> 14:55.862
Also, I'm pretty good
with chopsticks.

14:55.895 --> 14:58.231
Never hurts to display
a little manual dexterity.

14:58.265 --> 14:59.967
You know,
tends to impress.

15:01.434 --> 15:05.172
I will want a cocktail
to soothe my nerves, but...
(CHUCKLES)

15:05.205 --> 15:06.940
Why would you
be nervous?

15:08.341 --> 15:09.909
Have you seen you?

15:11.111 --> 15:14.114
You are smart
as well as beautiful,

15:14.147 --> 15:18.685
and I will need all the tools
in my toolkit
to dazzle you, so...

15:20.053 --> 15:21.721
No drink for me.

15:24.724 --> 15:26.693
Have one
after the appetizers.

15:27.427 --> 15:29.162
I'll be impressed by then.

15:30.530 --> 15:31.598
(CHUCKLES)

15:31.631 --> 15:34.167
**

15:37.237 --> 15:38.838
You have a fever.

15:38.871 --> 15:40.974
**

15:42.142 --> 15:44.811
He has a fever, and the rash
is fully materialized.

15:45.712 --> 15:46.879
Okay.
(CELLPHONE BEEPS)

15:49.149 --> 15:50.617
Here we go. (SIGHS)

15:51.818 --> 15:53.153
SECURITY GUARD 1:
Quarantine
has been approved.

15:53.186 --> 15:54.721
Yeah.

15:54.754 --> 15:58.925
**

15:58.958 --> 16:00.960
(PEOPLE WHISPERING
INDISTINCTLY)

16:03.630 --> 16:05.532
Can I have
everyone's attention?

16:05.565 --> 16:07.567
(WHISPERING STOPS)

16:09.136 --> 16:12.172
This emergency room
and everyone in it
is now under quarantine.

16:12.205 --> 16:14.074
(INDISTINCT MURMURING)

16:14.107 --> 16:16.009
We're hoping none of you
have been exposed,

16:16.043 --> 16:17.710
but a serious
respiratory virus

16:17.744 --> 16:19.112
has infected three patients.

16:19.146 --> 16:21.448
What?
This can't happen.

16:21.481 --> 16:23.816
We're starting everyone
on antivirals
just as a precaution.

16:23.850 --> 16:26.186
We'll also be bringing in
food and water,

16:26.219 --> 16:29.589
so if any of you have
any dietary restrictions,
please let us know now.

16:29.622 --> 16:31.624
You can't
make us stay here.
That's right.

16:31.658 --> 16:34.427
I-I can't... Especially not
if someone's seriously ill.

16:34.461 --> 16:36.096
We are legally entitled
to keep you for...
(BEEPING)

16:36.129 --> 16:37.364
They locked us in.

16:37.397 --> 16:39.032
(ALL SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

16:39.066 --> 16:41.301
Are we locked in?
Oh, no way.

16:41.334 --> 16:42.835
(MURMURING INTENSIFIES)

16:43.603 --> 16:45.072
I gotta get out.
Sir.

16:47.006 --> 16:48.308
(PEOPLE EXCLAIMING)

16:49.008 --> 16:50.210
Sorry.

16:50.243 --> 16:52.045
(GASPS AND EXCLAMATIONS)

16:52.079 --> 16:53.080
(GASPING)

16:54.647 --> 16:55.782
(GROANS)

16:58.685 --> 17:00.587
Like it or not,
no one's leaving.

17:00.620 --> 17:06.193
**

17:07.794 --> 17:09.762
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYS)

17:09.796 --> 17:14.834
**

17:14.867 --> 17:19.539
**

17:19.572 --> 17:24.144
**

17:24.177 --> 17:25.978
The decision to implement
the quarantine

17:26.012 --> 17:29.015
was made after consultation
with the Board.

17:29.048 --> 17:31.384
The CDC has been kept
fully informed,

17:31.418 --> 17:33.720
and we will be proceeding
in accordance
with all protocol...

17:36.022 --> 17:37.724
Shaun, Morgan, and Lim
are in there.

17:37.757 --> 17:39.359
And our patient
is out here.

17:39.392 --> 17:42.028
DR. PARK: There's still
no sign of the donor.
He's not answering my calls.

17:42.061 --> 17:44.697
I asked my contact
at San Jose PD
to do a home check-in.

17:45.232 --> 17:47.900
(CELLPHONE VIBRATING)

17:47.934 --> 17:49.269
(CELLPHONE BEEPS)

17:49.302 --> 17:50.403
Park.

17:51.771 --> 17:52.839
He's down there?

17:52.872 --> 17:54.207
How... Yeah,
put him on.

17:54.241 --> 17:56.176
It's Security... Kellan's
stuck in the quarantine.

17:56.209 --> 17:58.445
**

17:58.478 --> 18:00.513
I'll pass along anything
I hear from San Jose PD.

18:00.547 --> 18:04.584
**

18:06.853 --> 18:08.455
Tyler started
coughing.

18:08.488 --> 18:11.057
Let's up his antivirals.
Start high flow oxygen
and zosyn

18:11.090 --> 18:12.992
to counter
any underlying infection.

18:13.025 --> 18:15.395
Santa Pete has
a sigmoid volvulus,

18:15.428 --> 18:16.896
he needs surgery
very soon.

18:16.929 --> 18:20.433
My call ended
37 minutes ago.

18:20.467 --> 18:22.602
I'm supposed to be
somewhere else,
It's important.

18:22.635 --> 18:23.870
No, it's not.

18:23.903 --> 18:25.838
(ELECTRIC BUZZING)
(EXHALES SHAKILY)

18:25.872 --> 18:28.074
We need a non-surgical fix
to a bowel obstruction.

18:28.107 --> 18:30.210
Anyone?

18:30.243 --> 18:32.712
(BUZZING CONTINUES)

18:32.745 --> 18:38.851
**

18:38.885 --> 18:40.920
(RADIO STATIC CRACKLES)

18:47.760 --> 18:49.429
(BUZZING INTENSIFYING)

18:49.462 --> 18:51.931
(BUZZING CONTINUES AS NORMAL)

18:53.600 --> 18:54.801
Murphy.

18:55.835 --> 18:57.804
Mmm.
You got something?

19:00.072 --> 19:01.174
Not really.

19:01.908 --> 19:03.910
Anything at all.
Please.

19:07.447 --> 19:09.115
We...

19:09.782 --> 19:11.017
We usually...

19:11.718 --> 19:13.152
We...

19:13.186 --> 19:17.257
(BUZZING CONTINUES)
We usually make a hole and...

19:18.391 --> 19:21.661
And come at an obstruction
from the side,

19:21.694 --> 19:23.296
but we can't.

19:23.330 --> 19:26.032
We need to use
the existing holes.

19:27.534 --> 19:30.370
An endoscope risks tearing
right through the bowel.

19:30.403 --> 19:32.038
A saline enema
doesn't.

19:32.939 --> 19:34.674
And it might
untwist the bowel.

19:36.108 --> 19:38.578
Simple,
but it could work.

19:39.045 --> 19:40.112
Nice.

19:40.146 --> 19:43.216
**

19:43.883 --> 19:44.984
I'm fine.

19:45.017 --> 19:47.354
Do you have
your inhaler?
Of course I do.

19:49.055 --> 19:50.790
What were you
doing down here?

19:50.823 --> 19:52.325
This isn't my fault.

19:54.026 --> 19:56.263
If you hadn't
been working...
Kellan.

19:56.296 --> 19:58.130
I know you must
be scared.

19:58.164 --> 20:00.032
(SCOFFS)
I'm fine.

20:07.307 --> 20:09.008
I'm keeping this hat on
for luck.

20:09.709 --> 20:11.210
Here we go.

20:12.579 --> 20:14.581
I'm threading the tube
into the rectum.

20:15.382 --> 20:16.983
Now, slowly push
the saline.

20:17.016 --> 20:18.184
That's...
(INHALES SHARPLY)

20:18.217 --> 20:20.186
It's not
a pleasant experience.

20:20.219 --> 20:22.221
I'm getting some
resistance to flow.

20:22.255 --> 20:23.890
I must've reached
the obstruction.

20:23.923 --> 20:25.224
Push harder.
Hang in there, Pete.

20:25.258 --> 20:26.326
Call me Santa...

20:26.359 --> 20:27.827
Ahhh! (EXHALES SHARPLY)

20:27.860 --> 20:29.529
Keep pushing
the saline.

20:29.562 --> 20:30.963
I'm sorry, Santa.

20:30.997 --> 20:32.765
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

20:40.340 --> 20:42.442
(BREATHING STEADIES)

20:43.943 --> 20:45.211
I feel
so much better.

20:45.244 --> 20:49.782
**

20:49.816 --> 20:52.385
DR. REZNICK:
We've got you on a pretty
high dose of antivirals.

20:54.554 --> 20:56.623
TYLER:
So, what's next?

20:56.656 --> 20:58.157
We're debating
nitric oxide...

20:58.190 --> 21:01.193
(SLURRING)
No, I mean if this
doesn't turn around.

21:03.363 --> 21:04.997
What happens
to me next?

21:06.198 --> 21:07.367
ARDS.

21:08.234 --> 21:09.836
Then full respiratory failure.

21:11.137 --> 21:13.373
(COUGHS)

21:14.541 --> 21:16.976
Hey, I've got a new idea
for our first date.

21:18.545 --> 21:19.579
Archery.

21:19.612 --> 21:21.648
I used to compete
when I was young.

21:21.681 --> 21:22.915
(CHUCKLES WEAKLY)

21:22.949 --> 21:25.051
Basically,
you'd be showing off.

21:25.084 --> 21:26.819
(CHUCKLES)

21:26.853 --> 21:28.555
I can show you
some tricks.

21:28.588 --> 21:30.957
Teach you a spit-finger hook,
how to anchor...

21:30.990 --> 21:33.660
And then proceed
to demolish you.

21:33.693 --> 21:36.629
Well, that sounds like
a reason to live.
(CHUCKLES)

21:36.663 --> 21:42.369
**

21:42.402 --> 21:47.306
**

21:47.340 --> 21:49.342
(BIRDS CHIRPING)
(DOG BARKS IN THE DISTANCE)

21:50.977 --> 21:52.712
(VEHICLE APPROACHING)

21:58.284 --> 21:59.852
(ENGINE TURNS OFF)

21:59.886 --> 22:02.021
I'm here to take you
to your imaging appointment.

22:02.054 --> 22:03.456
DR. GLASSMAN: Where's Shaun?

22:03.490 --> 22:06.092
Shaun is quarantined
in the E.R.

22:06.125 --> 22:08.661
Quarantined? What, what...
What quarantine?

22:08.695 --> 22:12.632
Apparently for some highly
contagious, deadly virus.

22:12.665 --> 22:14.667
But Shaun sounds fine.

22:14.701 --> 22:16.569
Except for
some buzzing light

22:16.603 --> 22:17.870
and his concern
about lunch

22:17.904 --> 22:21.574
and you missing
your appointment
at the imaging clinic, so...

22:21.608 --> 22:24.411
Let's go.
Take me
to the hospital.

22:24.444 --> 22:26.413
We are going
to your appointment
and making sure

22:26.446 --> 22:28.347
your think-melon
remains tumor-free.

22:28.381 --> 22:30.116
Take me
to the hospital please.

22:30.149 --> 22:32.118
I'd like to help.
How?

22:32.151 --> 22:34.120
By taking your old job back
and saving the day?

22:34.153 --> 22:36.989
Putting on an "Outbreak" suit
and rescuing Shaun?

22:38.991 --> 22:40.292
(SIGHS)

22:40.326 --> 22:43.262
Some people may find
your sassy attitude appealing.

22:43.295 --> 22:44.697
I'm not one of them.

22:45.231 --> 22:46.733
And I am crushed.

22:46.766 --> 22:48.568
(KEYS JINGLE,
ENGINE STARTS)

22:56.075 --> 22:58.010
(DOOR OPENS)

22:58.044 --> 22:59.512
SECURITY GUARD 2:
Sir, I'm sorry. You can't...

22:59.546 --> 23:01.514
CLIFTON: (STAMMERING)
My wife's in there.

23:01.548 --> 23:03.516
Viola! Look, that's her.
I need to get in there.

23:03.550 --> 23:06.318
They're setting up
a room inside
for friends and family.

23:06.352 --> 23:07.720
Clifton,
what are you doing?

23:07.754 --> 23:10.457
Look, I'm coming in.
(STRUGGLING) Stop...
Let go of me!

23:10.490 --> 23:12.291
Calm down
or you're gonna get hurt.

23:12.324 --> 23:14.326
Stop.
This is all my fault.

23:14.360 --> 23:16.062
No.
If I'd put the crib together
like you asked...

23:16.596 --> 23:18.397
Forget about
the crib.

23:18.431 --> 23:20.032
I need you to take care
of yourself.

23:21.200 --> 23:22.869
Because if something
happens to me...

23:25.438 --> 23:27.607
...our son needs someone
to take care of him.

23:31.043 --> 23:32.044
(CHUCKLES)

23:33.546 --> 23:36.415
It's... It's a boy?

23:36.449 --> 23:38.751
I'm sorry I'm ruining
your surprise.

23:39.085 --> 23:40.086
No.

23:41.854 --> 23:43.055
(SNIFFLES)

23:43.690 --> 23:45.057
(EXHALES)

23:45.091 --> 23:48.194
Baby, I love you
so much.

23:48.227 --> 23:49.662
I love you, too.

23:49.696 --> 23:53.165
**

23:54.601 --> 23:55.935
(BREATHES SHAKILY)

23:56.603 --> 23:58.237
(SOFTLY) I love you.

23:58.270 --> 24:04.076
**

24:04.110 --> 24:07.614
**

24:07.647 --> 24:10.617
**

24:10.650 --> 24:11.718
(SOBBING)

24:11.751 --> 24:15.888
**

24:15.922 --> 24:19.091
**

24:19.125 --> 24:20.392
(SNIFFLES)

24:20.426 --> 24:23.395
**

24:23.429 --> 24:25.264
(CELLPHONE VIBRATING)

24:25.297 --> 24:28.935
**

24:28.968 --> 24:32.171
(VIBRATING CONTINUES)

24:35.141 --> 24:36.308
(CELLPHONE BEEPS,
VIBRATING STOPS)

24:36.342 --> 24:37.777
Dr. Shaun Murphy.

24:38.645 --> 24:40.246
Shaun?

24:40.279 --> 24:42.314
Why are you answering
our donor's phone?

24:43.583 --> 24:46.318
Because he's here
in quarantine.

24:46.352 --> 24:48.721
**

24:48.755 --> 24:50.623
(SIGHS)

24:53.660 --> 24:58.130
**

24:58.164 --> 25:03.102
**

25:03.135 --> 25:07.674
**

25:07.707 --> 25:11.744
**

25:11.778 --> 25:14.614
**

25:14.647 --> 25:16.348
(INDISTINCT MURMURING)

25:16.382 --> 25:18.818
What happened to the CDC
getting a team here today?

25:18.851 --> 25:21.821
They confirmed that it
started in Malaysia last week.

25:21.854 --> 25:23.389
Between the virologists
already there

25:23.422 --> 25:25.958
and the ones grounded
on the East Coast
because of the snowstorm...

25:25.992 --> 25:27.359
Stay on them.

25:28.260 --> 25:33.299
**

25:33.332 --> 25:35.001
What do we know
about the virus?

25:35.034 --> 25:38.170
Similar symptoms to SARS,
but much faster moving.

25:38.204 --> 25:39.839
Is Bob Cravens infected?

25:39.872 --> 25:41.140
Not so far.

25:41.173 --> 25:43.976
Currently Tyler Durnes,
the EMT,

25:44.010 --> 25:46.613
is the only person
displaying symptoms.

25:46.646 --> 25:48.480
I need his bone marrow.
I'd like to go in and get it.

25:48.514 --> 25:49.782
I'll comply
with all protocol.

25:49.816 --> 25:52.384
You're not hot zone certified.
None of us are.

25:52.418 --> 25:55.021
My leukemia patient
has no immune system.

25:55.054 --> 25:56.723
He'll die soon without
a marrow transplant.

25:56.756 --> 25:58.658
Well, then you best find him
another donor

25:58.691 --> 26:01.694
because no one,
or their bone marrow,
is leaving that quarantine.

26:01.728 --> 26:04.430
**

26:04.463 --> 26:06.666
Have you heard from County
about taking
our PICU transfers?

26:07.099 --> 26:13.105
**

26:13.139 --> 26:17.810
**

26:17.844 --> 26:23.349
**

26:23.382 --> 26:27.586
**

26:27.620 --> 26:29.221
**

26:31.090 --> 26:32.625
H-How are my O2 SATs?

26:34.060 --> 26:35.561
Holding steady.

26:35.594 --> 26:36.595
(SIGHS IN RELIEF)

26:38.264 --> 26:39.465
Do you want
to call anyone?

26:40.066 --> 26:42.735
(SHIVERING) Uh, I, uh...

26:42.769 --> 26:46.605
I... I thought about
letting my mom know...

26:46.639 --> 26:48.474
(VOICE BREAKING)
what was going on, but...

26:49.909 --> 26:52.979
She'd just worry about me
and feel bad she's not here.

26:53.746 --> 26:55.047
So...
(STEADYING BREATH)

26:56.315 --> 26:58.818
She... She knows I love her.

27:02.655 --> 27:03.823
(DOOR OPENS)

27:05.324 --> 27:06.425
How's it going
in here?

27:06.458 --> 27:07.894
(NORMAL VOICE) Dr. Reznick
was just telling me

27:07.927 --> 27:10.162
about some college
lesbian experiences...

27:11.798 --> 27:14.266
Was that just
my imagination?

27:14.300 --> 27:16.669
Actually, we were talking
about your mother.

27:16.703 --> 27:18.570
Interesting.
(CHUCKLES)

27:18.604 --> 27:23.109
**

27:23.142 --> 27:25.444
I don't like the drop
in his O2 SATs.

27:26.245 --> 27:27.814
Let's start him
on nitric oxide.

27:29.782 --> 27:31.150
(SIGHS)

27:31.183 --> 27:32.418
I knew you liked me.

27:32.451 --> 27:34.687
(CHUCKLES)

27:34.721 --> 27:40.492
**

27:40.526 --> 27:42.695
(CHRIS COUGHS)

27:42.729 --> 27:44.496
(STRAINING) He's
in this hospital?

27:44.530 --> 27:45.631
(CHUCKLES)

27:45.664 --> 27:47.599
Bob actually came through
for once.

27:47.633 --> 27:50.803
DR. MELENDEZ: Unfortunately,
we can't wait for him
to get out of quarantine.

27:50.837 --> 27:53.139
But we found an alternative
donor in the Bay Area.

27:53.172 --> 27:54.807
CHRIS: How compatible
are they?

27:54.841 --> 27:57.509
They share five out of eight
of your markers.

27:58.410 --> 28:00.612
Bob is a much better
match.

28:00.646 --> 28:02.849
I can't handle
marrow rejection,

28:02.882 --> 28:04.851
or having to repeat
this nightmare.

28:04.884 --> 28:08.154
(COUGHING)

28:16.362 --> 28:17.997
That's a symptom
of the MAC pneumonia.

28:18.030 --> 28:19.999
The antibiotics
aren't working.

28:20.032 --> 28:24.303
You need bone marrow,
or this infection is going
to kill you. Soon.

28:24.336 --> 28:25.972
Days, not weeks.

28:26.005 --> 28:28.841
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

28:33.545 --> 28:36.382
Seven years I've been
battling leukemia.

28:37.383 --> 28:39.752
Been through four
full courses of chemo,

28:39.786 --> 28:42.188
so many trips to the hospital
I've lost count.

28:42.989 --> 28:44.857
Just knowing my father
showed up,

28:46.058 --> 28:49.428
I'm grateful, relieved.

28:50.262 --> 28:51.263
(SIGHS)

28:53.165 --> 28:56.502
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

28:56.535 --> 28:58.905
I'm okay
if this is the end.

29:00.406 --> 29:01.908
I'd like to sign a DNR.

29:03.242 --> 29:05.744
Chris, the CDC will be here
tomorrow.

29:05.778 --> 29:08.347
If they can
identify the virus,
we can test Bob.

29:08.380 --> 29:11.617
If he's negative...
Whatever you can manage
before my heart stops,

29:11.650 --> 29:13.252
go for it.

29:16.288 --> 29:19.025
Please get me the form.

29:19.058 --> 29:24.596
**

29:24.630 --> 29:28.100
**

29:28.134 --> 29:31.703
**

29:31.737 --> 29:33.239
His fever's climbing.

29:33.272 --> 29:34.807
Give the nebulizer time
to work.

29:36.608 --> 29:39.178
Cooling blankets,
that could help.

29:39.211 --> 29:41.447
I'll go get some from
the supply closet.

29:42.815 --> 29:44.650
Put your mask back on.

29:44.683 --> 29:46.052
Why?

29:46.085 --> 29:47.553
Because
I'm infected.

29:48.921 --> 29:50.957
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYS)

29:50.990 --> 29:54.927
**

29:58.164 --> 30:00.232
(MONITOR BEEPING STEADILY)

30:00.266 --> 30:04.003
**

30:04.036 --> 30:05.404
(WEAKLY)
You got it, too?

30:06.338 --> 30:07.339
(SIGHS)

30:10.276 --> 30:13.112
(SHIVERING)
You guys any closer
to figuring this thing out?

30:13.712 --> 30:15.014
Afraid not.

30:15.047 --> 30:16.048
(SIGHS)

30:17.349 --> 30:19.418
On the bright side, I...

30:19.451 --> 30:21.487
I think I'm growing
on Morgan.

30:25.291 --> 30:27.026
(FLATLINE)

30:27.059 --> 30:31.597
**

30:31.630 --> 30:36.368
**

30:44.210 --> 30:45.611
DR. MELENDEZ: There's got
to be a way.

30:47.046 --> 30:48.680
You can't go in.

30:48.714 --> 30:51.183
Bob can't come out.
The marrow can't come out.

30:53.986 --> 30:55.621
What if it doesn't?

30:57.523 --> 30:59.959
What if the marrow
never leaves?

30:59.992 --> 31:03.195
Are we suggesting we put
a man with no immune system
into the quarantine?

31:03.229 --> 31:05.697
We expand the quarantine,
create a section
just for him.

31:07.733 --> 31:10.602
One of the doctors inside
could do the extraction
and the transplant.

31:10.636 --> 31:12.304
And then one
of two things happens.

31:12.338 --> 31:15.107
He stays in isolation
till we know
he hasn't been infected.

31:15.942 --> 31:17.343
Or it kills him.

31:19.578 --> 31:22.381
There's no way Andrews
will let us
expand the quarantine.

31:25.417 --> 31:26.652
Wish me luck.

31:28.520 --> 31:29.855
(DOOR OPENS)

31:29.888 --> 31:31.623
(FLATLINE)

31:31.657 --> 31:34.193
DR. LIM:
Going to 360 Joules.
Clear.

31:34.893 --> 31:36.996
(THUD)

31:37.029 --> 31:38.464
(RAPID BEEPING)

31:38.497 --> 31:41.100
(FLATLINE)

31:44.036 --> 31:46.305
We can crack his chest
and do cardiac massage.

31:46.338 --> 31:48.007
Dr. Reznick.
Have Petringa bring in

31:48.040 --> 31:49.575
the internal paddles
from the trauma bay...

31:49.608 --> 31:51.077
Morgan.

31:51.110 --> 31:52.778
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

31:52.811 --> 31:55.314
(FLATLINE CONTINUES)

31:55.347 --> 32:00.752
**

32:00.786 --> 32:04.656
**

32:04.690 --> 32:07.859
**

32:07.893 --> 32:12.131
**

32:12.164 --> 32:18.370
**

32:18.404 --> 32:20.072
(MUFFLED)
Hey, Doogie.

32:20.106 --> 32:21.440
(SNAPS)

32:21.473 --> 32:22.975
(CLEAR) You didn't hear me
talking to you?

32:23.009 --> 32:25.577
My sugar's crazy high. 650.

32:28.014 --> 32:31.050
That doesn't
make sense.

32:31.083 --> 32:34.220
I gave you the proper
dosage of insulin.

32:34.253 --> 32:35.687
10 units.

32:35.721 --> 32:36.989
10 units?

32:37.023 --> 32:39.691
10 units doesn't even make
a dent with me.

32:39.725 --> 32:41.927
You got a doctor around here
who knows what he's doing?

32:41.960 --> 32:43.629
(LOW ELECTRIC BUZZING)
I'm Dr. Shaun Murphy.

32:43.662 --> 32:46.265
I'll give you
another 10 units.

32:46.298 --> 32:47.933
Waste of time.
Make it 20.

32:47.966 --> 32:49.435
I'll give you 10.

32:49.468 --> 32:51.437
What's wrong with you?
You sound like an idiot.

32:51.470 --> 32:53.472
Don't be a jerk.
Mind your own business.

32:53.505 --> 32:55.474
Doc. Doc, I don't
feel so... (RETCHES)

32:55.507 --> 32:57.576
Ahhh!
What the hell?

32:57.609 --> 32:59.145
Did he just infect me?

32:59.178 --> 33:00.546
Possibly.
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

33:00.579 --> 33:02.714
I need to examine
your abdomen.

33:02.748 --> 33:05.251
**

33:05.284 --> 33:08.020
(LABORED BREATHING)

33:09.188 --> 33:10.989
Your obstruction
has returned.

33:11.023 --> 33:13.292
You need surgery, now.

33:13.325 --> 33:14.926
But we're stuck in here.

33:15.661 --> 33:17.196
And there's
no operating room.

33:17.229 --> 33:18.997
(HEAVY BREATHING CONTINUES)

33:19.031 --> 33:21.100
We will have
to improvise.

33:21.133 --> 33:22.134
(PETE WHIMPERS)

33:24.370 --> 33:27.206
**

33:27.239 --> 33:29.908
**

33:29.941 --> 33:31.477
There's no Neptune machine.

33:31.510 --> 33:34.580
Without suction,
the surgical field
will be filled with blood.

33:34.613 --> 33:38.284
We can use the wall suction,
set to continuous.

33:38.317 --> 33:39.351
That'll do.

33:39.385 --> 33:42.921
**

33:42.954 --> 33:46.792
**

33:46.825 --> 33:49.595
No electrocautery
to control the bleeding.

33:49.628 --> 33:51.363
You'll have to do this
combat style.

33:51.397 --> 33:52.864
(DR. LIM COUGHS)

33:52.898 --> 33:55.234
Tie off each artery
before you cut.

33:55.267 --> 33:57.336
(INTENSE MUSIC PLAYS)

33:57.369 --> 33:59.405
**

33:59.438 --> 34:02.774
**

34:02.808 --> 34:06.945
**

34:06.978 --> 34:12.184
**

34:12.218 --> 34:15.987
**

34:16.021 --> 34:17.856
(DR. LIM BREATHES HEAVILY)

34:17.889 --> 34:19.391
Dr. Reznick.

34:20.992 --> 34:23.595
Are you ready?
Because I think we are.

34:29.101 --> 34:30.402
I'll go
get the patient.

34:31.403 --> 34:33.505
(DR. LIM COUGHS)

34:33.539 --> 34:38.177
**

34:38.210 --> 34:40.279
You should lie down.

34:40.312 --> 34:44.750
**

34:44.783 --> 34:50.189
**

34:50.222 --> 34:51.257
(SIGHS)

34:51.290 --> 34:56.228
**

34:56.262 --> 34:59.865
**

34:59.898 --> 35:02.100
**

35:02.134 --> 35:05.103
(MONITOR BEEPING STEADILY)

35:05.137 --> 35:08.607
**

35:08.640 --> 35:09.641
He's out.

35:10.476 --> 35:11.710
Scalpel.

35:11.743 --> 35:16.047
**

35:16.081 --> 35:20.386
**

35:20.419 --> 35:24.055
**

35:24.089 --> 35:26.258
**

35:26.292 --> 35:29.328
DR. MELENDEZ:
If we expand the quarantine,
I can do the transplant.

35:29.361 --> 35:30.896
The only technical breach
will be...

35:33.799 --> 35:39.037
**

35:39.070 --> 35:41.139
She's infected.

35:41.173 --> 35:44.276
(CELLPHONE RINGING, VIBRATING)

35:47.679 --> 35:48.914
Melendez.

35:50.682 --> 35:51.683
Yeah.

35:53.018 --> 35:55.454
(MONITOR BEEPING STEADILY)

35:55.487 --> 35:57.723
Take down the adhesions
on the sigmoid.

36:00.559 --> 36:01.693
How are his vitals?

36:04.029 --> 36:05.297
NURSE VILLANUEVA:
Holding steady, Doctor.

36:07.999 --> 36:09.167
DR. REZNICK:
That's dead bowel.

36:12.804 --> 36:14.072
DR. MURPHY: It's perforated.

36:14.105 --> 36:15.140
Damn it.

36:15.173 --> 36:18.810
**

36:18.844 --> 36:20.512
**

36:20.546 --> 36:22.448
(CRASH IN DISTANCE)
NURSE PETRINGA:
I need a doctor!

36:22.481 --> 36:23.849
Petringa
needs help.

36:25.551 --> 36:26.985
DR. REZNICK: If I don't
secure these clamps,

36:27.018 --> 36:28.354
there'll be stool
everywhere.

36:30.756 --> 36:32.123
Murphy, go.

36:32.157 --> 36:35.193
(DISTANT PANICKED MURMURING)

36:35.227 --> 36:38.964
**

36:38.997 --> 36:42.701
**

36:42.734 --> 36:46.838
(MACHINE BEEPING RAPIDLY,
FLATLINE)

36:53.445 --> 36:55.447
(BEEPING STOPS)

37:03.021 --> 37:04.155
He signed a DNR.

37:04.189 --> 37:05.190
He shouldn't have.

37:06.725 --> 37:08.226
This is battery.

37:08.260 --> 37:09.561
He doesn't need
to die.

37:09.595 --> 37:11.029
We're gonna get
his donor's marrow.

37:11.863 --> 37:13.164
Andrews agreed
to the plan?

37:13.765 --> 37:16.368
Not yet.
(SIGHS)

37:16.402 --> 37:18.069
If he doesn't, we'll think
of something else.

37:23.809 --> 37:30.015
**

37:30.048 --> 37:34.320
**

37:34.353 --> 37:36.087
(KELLAN BREATHING HEAVILY)

37:36.121 --> 37:38.089
KELLAN: He said he was
feeling lightheaded.

37:38.123 --> 37:41.192
(ELECTRIC BUZZING)

37:42.594 --> 37:45.063
SECURITY GUARD 1:
I hear you,
but please stay back.

37:45.096 --> 37:49.801
**

37:49.835 --> 37:51.236
He's...
WOMAN: Is he infected?

37:51.269 --> 37:52.938
From when Santa
vomited on him?

37:52.971 --> 37:54.406
He should go
to isolation.

37:54.440 --> 37:57.643
(INDISTINCT MURMURING)

37:57.676 --> 38:00.746
He's in...
(BUZZING INCREASES)

38:00.779 --> 38:02.080
...hypoglycemic shock.

38:02.814 --> 38:04.049
Give him D50.

38:04.082 --> 38:07.719
**

38:07.753 --> 38:10.989
(BUZZING GETS LOUDER)

38:11.022 --> 38:13.692
(LABORED BREATHING)

38:15.427 --> 38:18.697
(KELLAN COUGHING)

38:19.130 --> 38:20.198
It's spreading.

38:20.231 --> 38:21.232
Kellan!

38:21.967 --> 38:23.469
(GASPING, COUGHING)

38:23.502 --> 38:25.136
(BANGING ON DOOR)
DR. PARK: Kellan!

38:27.238 --> 38:28.807
(GASPING, COUGHING)

38:28.840 --> 38:29.975
Kellan!

38:30.008 --> 38:32.411
Kellan! Kellan!
(BANGING CONTINUES)

38:32.444 --> 38:34.245
Kellan!

38:34.279 --> 38:35.981
(BUZZING GETS LOUDER)

38:36.014 --> 38:38.083
( DECK THE HALLS
PLAYS OVER SPEAKERS)

38:38.116 --> 38:42.988
**

38:43.021 --> 38:46.257
**

38:46.291 --> 38:47.726
ATTENDANT:
Dr. Glassman?

38:50.729 --> 38:51.797
Hi.

38:51.830 --> 38:53.499
We got what we needed
for images.

38:53.532 --> 38:54.600
You are okay to go.

38:54.633 --> 38:56.602
We'll send them
to Dr. Blaize.

38:56.635 --> 38:58.036
Anything I should
be worried about?

38:58.069 --> 39:00.338
You're seeing Dr. Blaize
before the holiday?

39:02.474 --> 39:04.810
As a matter of fact,
I'm seeing her now.

39:04.843 --> 39:07.813
So, I could just show her
the hard copy.

39:07.846 --> 39:09.981
I'm not supposed
to do that.
Oh, no. I know.

39:10.015 --> 39:11.850
I've been a neurosurgeon
for, like, 100 years.

39:11.883 --> 39:13.819
I understand protocol.
I'm not gonna look at it.

39:13.852 --> 39:15.387
I just want
to move things along.

39:19.525 --> 39:20.526
Thank you.

39:35.707 --> 39:38.744
(PAPER RUSTLING)

39:46.485 --> 39:47.653
It's back.

39:47.686 --> 39:51.457
(SHUDDERS)

39:51.490 --> 39:53.625
(SOLEMN MUSIC PLAYS)

39:53.659 --> 39:57.529
**

39:57.563 --> 39:59.798
**

40:02.801 --> 40:04.536
(INDISTINCT CHATTER
IN DISTANCE)

40:04.570 --> 40:08.073
**

40:08.106 --> 40:10.576
**

40:10.609 --> 40:11.610
DR. REZNICK: Suction.

40:14.980 --> 40:17.649
I must've nicked a branch
of the inferior
mesenteric artery.

40:17.683 --> 40:18.717
I can't see where.

40:18.750 --> 40:20.586
Can you feel it?

40:20.619 --> 40:24.890
**

40:24.923 --> 40:27.959
I think so.
Use your finger
to plug the hole.

40:29.427 --> 40:30.629
(HISSES)

40:31.730 --> 40:32.998
Now what?

40:35.534 --> 40:36.735
Dr. Lim?

40:36.768 --> 40:41.607
**

40:41.640 --> 40:44.710
**

40:44.743 --> 40:46.612
(HYPERVENTILATING)
(INDISTINCT YELLING)

40:46.645 --> 40:48.446
SECURITY GUARD 1:
Everyone,
calm down.

40:48.480 --> 40:50.415
Hey, Kellan!
Kellan! Look at me!

40:50.448 --> 40:52.217
Look at me!
Breathe!

40:52.250 --> 40:54.620
Can... Can you hear me?
Can you hear me?

40:54.653 --> 40:55.721
(LOUD BUZZING)

40:55.754 --> 40:56.988
(HARSH ZAPS)

40:57.022 --> 40:59.290
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

40:59.324 --> 41:00.391
(ECHOING CHATTER)

41:00.425 --> 41:01.760
(HYPERVENTILATING)

41:02.761 --> 41:04.530
(COUGHING,
INDISTINCT YELLING)

41:04.563 --> 41:06.732
(BUZZING CRESCENDOS)

41:10.569 --> 41:12.638
(HYPERVENTILATING)
(INDISTINCT YELLING CONTINUES)

41:15.273 --> 41:16.307
Help my son!

41:18.209 --> 41:19.444
(ELECTRICITY SPARKS)
(ALL SOUND STOPS)

41:19.477 --> 41:21.479
( SILENT NIGHT PLAYING)

41:23.815 --> 41:28.319
* Silent night

41:28.353 --> 41:32.958
* Holy night

41:32.991 --> 41:37.195
* All is calm

41:37.228 --> 41:42.133
* All is bright

41:42.167 --> 41:46.772
* Round yon Virgin

41:46.805 --> 41:51.209
* Mother and Child

41:51.242 --> 41:55.113
* Holy Infant

41:55.146 --> 42:00.819
* So tender and mild

42:00.852 --> 42:05.223
* Sleep in heavenly

42:05.256 --> 42:09.795
* Peace

42:09.828 --> 42:14.700
* Sleep in heavenly

42:14.733 --> 42:18.036
* Peace

42:18.069 --> 42:21.406
**

42:24.542 --> 42:30.181
**

42:30.215 --> 42:35.854
**

42:35.887 --> 42:39.958
**

42:39.991 --> 42:44.029
**

42:44.062 --> 42:48.099
**

42:48.133 --> 42:52.070
**

42:52.103 --> 42:54.472
**
